# Git Workflow

## Branch Naming

```
main              # stable, soumission-ready
<prenom>          # branche personnelle d'exploration (ex: anthony, skows)
feat/<feature>    # nouvelle feature engineering ou modèle
exp/<experiment>  # expérimentation isolée
fix/<bug>         # correction
```

## Commit Convention

```
<type>: <short description>

Types: feat | fix | exp | data | model | docs | refactor
```

Examples:
```
feat: add lgbm model class with is_unbalance
exp: test catboost on mcc target encoded features
fix: correct amount parsing for negative values
model: register lightgbm v2 in mlflow
```

## Rules

- Never commit directly to `main` without review
- Never commit `dataset/` changes (read-only)
- Never commit `.joblib` model files
- Each author works on their own named branch
- Merge to `main` only when submission-ready
